    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="258"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72112/1381</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to President
                            <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. President</hi>: I enclose a copy of the English
                        note<note n="80" xml:id="d258fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1915Supp#pg_168">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1915, supp., p.
                        168</ref>.</note> we have received in reply to ours of March 30th. It was
                    intended to have this note published simultaneously in England and the United
                    States Wednesday morning, but last night I received a telegram from Mr.
                        Page,<note n="81" xml:id="d258fn2">Not printed.</note> saying that Sir
                    Edward Grey would have ready within a week another note dealing with the
                    practical questions relating to shipping, and he therefore requested that
                    publication be delayed until the latter note had been delivered.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
